OL,3,CHealth trusts asked to draw up cost
OL,4,Csavings to cover #300m budget shortfall
OL,6,FMr Swann has claimed an additional
OL,7,F#500 million he was allocated in the
OL,8,Fbudget agreed by the Stormont
OL,9,FExecutive last week falls well short
OL,10,Fof what is required to maintain health
OL,11,Fservice provision at current levels.
OL,13,FHe voted against the spending plan and
OL,14,Fhas refused to rule out resigning if
OL,15,Fthe budget is approved by the Assembly
OL,16,Fin its current form.
